#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:237
msgid "Close spider extension"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:244
msgid ""
"Closes a spider automatically when some conditions are met, using a specific "
"closing reason for each condition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:247
msgid ""
"The conditions for closing a spider can be configured through the following "
"settings:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:250
msgid ":setting:`CLOSESPIDER_TIMEOUT`"
msgstr ":setting:`CLOSESPIDER_TIMEOUT`"

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:251
msgid ":setting:`CLOSESPIDER_TIMEOUT_NO_ITEM`"
msgstr ":setting:`CLOSESPIDER_TIMEOUT_NO_ITEM`"

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:252
msgid ":setting:`CLOSESPIDER_ITEMCOUNT`"
msgstr ":setting:`CLOSESPIDER_ITEMCOUNT`"

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:253
msgid ":setting:`CLOSESPIDER_PAGECOUNT`"
msgstr ":setting:`CLOSESPIDER_PAGECOUNT`"

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:254
msgid ":setting:`CLOSESPIDER_ERRORCOUNT`"
msgstr ":setting:`CLOSESPIDER_ERRORCOUNT`"

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:258
msgid ""
"When a certain closing condition is met, requests which are currently in the "
"downloader queue (up to :setting:`CONCURRENT_REQUESTS` requests) are still "
"processed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:265
msgid "CLOSESPIDER_TIMEOUT"
msgstr "CLOSESPIDER_TIMEOUT"

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:267 ../../../topics/extensions.rst:279
#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:291 ../../../topics/extensions.rst:303
#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:315 ../../../topics/extensions.rst:328
msgid "Default: ``0``"
msgstr "預設值：``0``"

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:269
msgid ""
"An integer which specifies a number of seconds. If the spider remains open "
"for more than that number of seconds, it will be automatically closed with "
"the reason ``closespider_timeout``. If zero (or non set), spiders won't be "
"closed by timeout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:277
msgid "CLOSESPIDER_TIMEOUT_NO_ITEM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:281
msgid ""
"An integer which specifies a number of seconds. If the spider has not "
"produced any items in the last number of seconds, it will be closed with the "
"reason ``closespider_timeout_no_item``. If zero (or non set), spiders won't "
"be closed regardless if it hasn't produced any items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:289
msgid "CLOSESPIDER_ITEMCOUNT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:293
msgid ""
"An integer which specifies a number of items. If the spider scrapes more "
"than that amount and those items are passed by the item pipeline, the spider "
"will be closed with the reason ``closespider_itemcount``. If zero (or non "
"set), spiders won't be closed by number of passed items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:301
msgid "CLOSESPIDER_PAGECOUNT"
msgstr "CLOSESPIDER_PAGECOUNT"

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:305
msgid ""
"An integer which specifies the maximum number of responses to crawl. If the "
"spider crawls more than that, the spider will be closed with the reason "
"``closespider_pagecount``. If zero (or non set), spiders won't be closed by "
"number of crawled responses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:313
msgid "CLOSESPIDER_PAGECOUNT_NO_ITEM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:317
msgid ""
"An integer which specifies the maximum number of consecutive responses to "
"crawl without items scraped. If the spider crawls more consecutive responses "
"than that and no items are scraped in the meantime, the spider will be "
"closed with the reason ``closespider_pagecount_no_item``. If zero (or not "
"set), spiders won't be closed by number of crawled responses with no items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:326
msgid "CLOSESPIDER_ERRORCOUNT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/extensions.rst:330
msgid ""
"An integer which specifies the maximum number of errors to receive before "
"closing the spider. If the spider generates more than that number of errors, "
"it will be closed with the reason ``closespider_errorcount``. If zero (or "
"non set), spiders won't be closed by number of errors."
msgstr ""

